The paper proposes a method for improving the calibration of classification models, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically mentions deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. The method is based on a non-parametric representation using a latent Gaussian process, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also includes a theoretical analysis of the relationship between calibration and over- and underconfidence, which is a statistical topic (cs.STAT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.STAT, and cs.CL.
